text.section:
Youths participating in the Corps shall work in projects which do the following:
Preserve, maintain, and enhance environmentally important lands and waters;
Work on public works projects in urban and rural areas;
Conserve, maintain, improve, and develop natural resources in urban and rural areas;
Assist in emergency operations, such as natural disaster relief and the rescue of lost and injured individuals;
Assist in fire prevention and suppression;
Directly contribute to the conservation of energy;
Contribute toward making public facilities accessible to individuals with disabilities; and
Assist other State agencies in developing, rehabilitating, and restoring parklands, recreational facilities, historical resources, fish spawning and rearing habitats, wildlife habitats, and the Chesapeake Bay.
